  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nAccording to the [design guidelines](https://app.zeplin.io/project/5a55d587ba304eed4d2c942f/screen/5b5abafd892d5c933636787d), the reply area/box in a chat should be scrollable to see the full message. Currently it's not.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/47293301-06637b00-d60a-11e8-8670-f2353f710e48.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nThe area can't be scrolled: \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/47293218-ce5c3800-d609-11e8-9f58-9195a638ba30.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\nTry to reply to a long message in 1-1 or public chat.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Oct 22, nightly\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
